      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Outer try-catch in +page.server.ts is redundant since fetchAllRepoData already handles all errors internally",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "src/routes/+page.server.ts",
          "src/lib/utils/github.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "+page.server.ts line 15-19: wraps fetchAllRepoData in try-catch, but fetchAllRepoData delegates to fetchRepoData which delegates to fetchJson, and all failures are already caught and converted to null at the inner layers",
          "The outer catch can only fire if Promise.all itself throws (an engine-level failure) or if the .map/.filter on project arrays throws, neither of which is a network error"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Either remove the outer try-catch (since the callee already guarantees no throws for network failures) or, if defensive coding at the SvelteKit load boundary is intentional, add a comment explaining that this guards against unexpected non-network failures rather than duplicating the network error handling.",
