    "review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::artefact_hardcoded_owner_url": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::artefact_hardcoded_owner_url",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Artefacts.svelte hardcodes GitHub owner URL prefix instead of deriving from data contract",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "mid_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/components/Artefacts.svelte",
          "src/lib/data/artefacts.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Artefacts.svelte line 25 constructs URLs as 'https://github.com/JasonWarrenUK/{artefact.repo}', hardcoding the owner. In contrast, ProjectCard.svelte line 123 uses 'https://github.com/{project.repo}' where the repo field already contains 'owner/repo'. The Artefact type's repo field contains only the repo name (e.g., 'nihilistic-onboarder'), while Project's repo field contains 'owner/repo' (e.g., 'JasonWarrenUK/sparker'). This inconsistency means the two parallel data paths use different URL construction strategies at the presentation boundary."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Change artefacts.ts repo values to include the owner prefix (e.g., 'JasonWarrenUK/nihilistic-onboarder') and update Artefacts.svelte to use 'https://github.com/{artefact.repo}' for consistency with ProjectCard. This aligns both data models on the same repo path convention.",
