      "id": "review::.::holistic::naming_quality::fetchJson_hides_null",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "fetchJson name does not communicate that it returns null on HTTP failure",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "naming_quality",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/utils/github.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "fetchJson (line 16) returns Promise<unknown> but actually returns null when fetchGitHub returns null on HTTP failure. The name 'fetchJson' implies it fetches and parses JSON, but the null-on-failure behavior is hidden. Callers must know to check for null, which the name does not suggest."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Rename to fetchJsonOrNull or tryFetchJson to communicate the nullable return semantics, matching the pattern where fetchGitHub already returns Promise<Response | null>. Alternatively, add the null to the return type annotation: Promise<unknown | null>.",
