    "review::.::holistic::type_safety::fetchJson_untyped_return": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::type_safety::fetchJson_untyped_return",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "fetchJson returns Promise<unknown> but can return null; callers get no type guidance on possible shapes",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "type_safety",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/utils/github.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "fetchJson (line 16) returns Promise<unknown> which technically covers null, but callers must independently know what shapes to expect. The function returns null when fetchGitHub returns null, or the parsed JSON otherwise. A return type of Promise<unknown | null> would be more explicit, though the real improvement would be a generic overload or documenting the null case."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Change the return type to Promise<unknown | null> to explicitly signal the null case. Alternatively, consider making fetchJson generic with a type guard parameter: async function fetchJson<T>(url: string, guard: (data: unknown) => data is T): Promise<T | null> to push type narrowing into the fetch call.",
