    "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::type_guard_contract_gap": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::type_guard_contract_gap",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "isRepoResponse claims to validate RepoResponse shape but does not verify all field types",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "contract_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "src/lib/utils/github.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "isRepoResponse (line 29) returns 'data is RepoResponse' but only validates typeof for stargazers_count and updated_at. The RepoResponse interface also includes open_issues_count: number and language: string | null, neither of which has typeof validation. A caller trusting the type guard would assume all fields are type-safe, but open_issues_count could be a non-number value."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Add typeof (data as RepoResponse).open_issues_count === 'number' to the guard. For language, check typeof === 'string' || value === null. This makes the guard's implementation match its stated contract.",
